Logistic regression

balance default . Default $Y$ .

$$ Y = \begin{cases} 0, & \text{if No;} \\ 1, & \text{if Yes.} \end{cases} $$

$X$ default .

$$ p(X) = \mathbb P (Y = 1 | X)$$

,

$$ 1 - p(X) = \mathbb P (Y = 0 | X)$$

Logistic regression .

$$ p(X) = \frac{e^{\theta_0 + \theta_1 X}}{1 + e^{\theta_0 + \theta_1 X}} $$

$\theta$ $X$ $p(X)$ 0 1 .

, , $p(X)$ log odds logit transformation .

$$ \log \left( \frac{p(X)}{1 - p(X)}\right) = \theta_0 + \theta_1 X $$

Maximum likelihood method

$\theta$ maximum likelihood estimation (MLE) .

$\{x_i, y_i \}$ , logistic regression $\theta_0, \theta_1$ , likelihood .

$$ \ell (\theta_0, \theta_1) = \prod_{i:y_i=1} p(x_i) \prod_{i:y_i=0}(1-p(x_i)) $$

$$p(x_i) = p_i = \frac{e^{\theta_0 + \theta_1 x_i}}{1 + e^{\theta_0 + \theta_1 x_i}} = \frac{1}{1 + e^{-\theta_0 - \theta_1 x_i}} $$

$\theta_0, \theta_1$ .

$\hat \theta_0, \hat \theta_1$ $\ell (\theta_0, \theta_1)$ .

$$ \hat \theta_0, \hat \theta_1 = \arg \max_{\theta_0, \theta_1} \ell (\theta_0, \theta_1) $$

log-likelihood .

$$ \hat \theta_0, \hat \theta_1 = \arg \max_{\theta_0, \theta_1} \log \ell (\theta_0, \theta_1) = \arg \max_{\theta_0, \theta_1} \sum_{i=1}^{N} \left[ y_i \log(p_i) + (1 - y_i)\log(1- p_i) \right]$$

$\hat \theta_0, \hat \theta_1$ $X$ default .

$$ \hat p(X) = \frac{e^{\hat \theta_0 + \hat \theta_1 X}}{1 + e^{\hat \theta_0 + \hat \theta_1 X}} $$

.

$$ \log \left( \frac{p(X)}{1 - p(X)}\right) = \theta_0 + \theta_1 X_1 + \cdots + \theta_p X_p $$

,

$$ p(X) = \frac{e^{\theta_0 + \theta_1 X_1 + \cdots + \theta_p X_p}}{1 + e^{\theta_0 + \theta_1 X_1 + \cdots + \theta_p X_p}} $$

gradient vector

.

.

$$ c(\boldsymbol{\theta}) = \left\{\begin{array}{lr} -\log(p), & \text{if } y = 1\\ -\log(1 - p), & \text{if } y = 0\\ \end{array}\right. $$

, log-likelihood

$$ J(\boldsymbol{\theta}) = -\frac{1}{N} \sum_{i=1}^{N} \left[ y_i \log(p_i) + (1 - y_i)\log(1- p_i) \right]$$ , $$ \ p_i = \sigma(\boldsymbol{\theta} \cdot x_i) = \frac{1}{1 + \exp( - \boldsymbol{\theta} \cdot x_i)} = \frac{1}{1 + \exp( - \theta_0 - x_{i1} \theta_1 - \cdots - x_{ip} \theta_p )}. $$

Gradient vector

$$ \sigma(t) = \frac{1}{1 + \exp(-t)} $$ $$ \frac{d}{d t}\sigma(t) = \sigma(t) (1 - \sigma(t))$$ , .

\begin{align*} \frac{\partial }{\partial \theta_j} J(\theta) &= -\frac{1}{N} \sum_{i=1}^{N} \left[ y_i \frac{ \frac{\partial }{\partial \theta_j} \sigma(\theta \cdot x_i)}{\sigma(\theta \cdot x_i)} + (1 - y_i) \frac{ \frac{\partial }{\partial \theta_j} \left\{ 1 - \sigma(\theta \cdot x_i) \right\} }{1 - \sigma(\theta \cdot x_i)} \right]\\ &= -\frac{1}{N} \sum_{i=1}^{N} \left[ y_i \frac{\sigma(\theta \cdot x_i)(1 - \sigma(\theta \cdot x_i)) }{\sigma(\theta \cdot x_i)}x_{ij} + (1 - y_i) \frac{ \sigma(\theta \cdot x_i)(1 - \sigma(\theta \cdot x_i)) } {1 - \sigma(\theta \cdot x_i)}x_{ij} \right] \\ &= - \frac{1}{N} \sum_{i=1}^{N} \left[ y_i - \sigma(\theta \cdot x_i) y_i - \sigma(\theta \cdot x_i) + \sigma(\theta \cdot x_i) y_i \right] x_{ij} \\ & = \frac{1}{N} \sum_{i=1}^{N} \left[ \sigma(\theta \cdot x_i) - y_i\right] x_{ij} \\ & = \frac{1}{N} \mathbf x_j^{\top} ( \sigma(\mathbf X \theta) - \mathbf y). \end{align*}

gradient vector \begin{equation*} \nabla_\theta J (\theta) = \frac{1}{N} \mathbf X^{\top} ( \sigma(\mathbf X \theta) - \mathbf y) = \frac{1}{N} \mathbf X^{\top} \left( \frac{1}{1 + \exp(- \mathbf X \theta)} - \mathbf y \right) \end{equation*} ,

$\boldsymbol{\theta}$ $\boldsymbol{\theta}^{\text{(next step)}}$ .

$$ \boldsymbol{\theta}^{\text{(next step)}} = \boldsymbol{\theta} - \eta \nabla_\theta J (\theta) $$

, gradient $\theta$ .

In[8]:
Xb = np.c_[np.ones((X.shape[0], 1)), X]

eta = 0.05
n_iteration = 20000
N = len(y)

theta = np.array([[0],[0]])
evolution = np.ravel(theta)

for _ in range(n_iteration):
    grad = 1 / N * Xb.T @ ( 1 / (1 + np.exp(-Xb @ theta)) - y.reshape(-1,1))
    # update theta
    theta = theta - eta * grad
    evolution = np.vstack((evolution, np.ravel(theta)))

log-likelihood .

In[10]:
def llf(theta, X, y):
    llh = 0
    for i in range(X.shape[0]):
        p = 1 / (1 + np.exp(-  X[i,:] @ theta))
        llh += y[i] * np.log(p) + (1 - y[i]) * np.log(1 - p)
    return llh

$Y$ $K$ . $k=1, \cdots, K$

$$ \mathbb P (Y = k | X) = \frac{e^{\theta^{(k)}_0 + \theta^{(k)}_1 X_1 + \cdots + \theta^{(k)}_p X_p}}{\sum_{\ell=1}^{K}e^{\theta^{(\ell)}_0 + \theta^{(\ell)}_1 X_1 + \cdots + \theta^{(\ell)}_p X_p}} $$

( $K$ , $K-1$ .)

$k$ $\theta^{(k)}_0, \theta^{(k)}_1, \cdots, \theta^{(k)}_p$ $1+p$ .

  • $(K - 1) \times (1 + p)$ .

multinomial regression softmax regression .

( , regression discriminant analysis .)

- cross entropy

Multi-class classification cross entropy .

Cross entropy .

$y_i$ ($p_i^{(k)}$ ) .

Cross entropy .

$K$ . , $ y_i \in \{ 1, \cdots, K \}$.

$p_{i}^{(k)}$ .

$$ p_{i}^{(k)} = P(y_i = k | x_i, \Theta ) = \frac{\exp(\theta^{(k)} \cdot x_i)}{\sum_{\ell=1}^{K} \exp(\theta^{(\ell)} \cdot x_i)} $$

$$\Theta = \begin{bmatrix} \theta^{(1)} & \theta^{(2)} & \cdots & \theta^{(K)} \end{bmatrix}$$

,

$$ \theta^{(k)} = \begin{bmatrix} \theta^{(k)}_0 & \theta^{(k)}_1 & \cdots & \theta^{(k)}_p \end{bmatrix}^{\top} $$

.

Cross entropy .

$$ J(\Theta) = -\frac{1}{N} \sum_{i=1}^{N} \sum_{\ell = 1}^{K} y_i^{(\ell)} \log p_{i}^{(\ell)} $$

,

$$ y_i^{(\ell)} = \mathbb {I}_{\{ y_i=\ell \}}. $$

Gradient for softmax

.

$J$ $\theta^{(k)}$ .

$$ \nabla_{\theta^{(k)}} J (\Theta) = \begin{bmatrix} \frac{\partial J(\Theta)}{\partial \theta_0^{(k)}} \\ \frac{\partial J(\Theta)}{\partial \theta_1^{(k)}} \\ \vdots \\ \frac{\partial J(\Theta)}{\partial \theta_p^{(k)}} \end{bmatrix} = \frac{1}{N} \sum_{i=1}^{N} ( p_i^{(k)} - y_i^{(k)} ) x_i .$$

\begin{align*} \frac{\partial J(\Theta)}{\partial \theta_j^{(k)}} &= -\frac{1}{N} \sum_{i=1}^{N} \sum_{\ell = 1}^{K} \frac{\partial}{\partial \theta_j^{(k)}} y_i^{(\ell)} \log p_{(i)}^{(\ell)} \\ &= -\frac{1}{N} \sum_{i=1}^{N} \sum_{\ell = 1}^{K} y_i^{(\ell)} \frac{\partial \log p^{(\ell)}_i }{\partial p^{(\ell)}_i} \frac{\partial p^{(\ell)}_i}{\partial a^{(k)}} \frac{\partial a^{(k)}}{\partial \theta_{j}^{(k)}} \end{align*}

$$ a^{(k)} = \theta^{(k)} \cdot x_i $$

$$ \frac{{\partial a^{(k)}}}{\partial \theta_{j}^{(k)}} = x_{ij}. $$

$$\frac{\partial J(\Theta)}{\partial \theta_j^{(k)}} = -\frac{1}{N} \sum_{i=1}^{N} \sum_{\ell = 1}^{K} \frac{y^{(\ell)}_i}{p^{(\ell)}_i} \frac{\partial p^{(\ell)}_i}{\partial a^{(k)}} x_{ij}.$$

, $\ell = k$ , $$ \frac{\partial p^{(\ell)}_i}{\partial a^{(k)}} = \frac{\partial p^{(\ell)}_i}{\partial a^{(\ell)}} = \frac{\partial}{\partial a^{(\ell)}} \frac{\exp(a^{(\ell)})}{\sum_{m=1}^{K} \exp(a^{(m)})} = \frac{\exp(a^{(\ell)})\sum_{m=1}^{K} \exp(a^{(m)}) - \exp(a^{(\ell)}) \exp(a^{(\ell)})}{ (\sum_{m=1}^{K} \exp(a^{(m)}) )^2 } = p^{(\ell)}_i \left( 1 - p^{(\ell)}_i \right) $$ , $\ell \neq k$ $$ \frac{\partial p^{(\ell)}_i}{\partial a^{(k)}} = - \frac{ \exp(a^{(\ell)}) \exp(a^{(k)})}{ (\sum_{m=1}^{K} \exp(a^{(m)}) )^2 } = - p^{(k)}_i p^{(\ell)}_i$$ .

, \begin{align*} \frac{\partial J(\Theta)}{\partial \theta_j^{(k)}} &= -\frac{1}{N} \sum_{i=1}^{N} \left( y_i^{(k)} (1 - p_i^{(k)} ) - \sum_{\ell \neq k} p_i^{(k)} y_i^{(\ell)} \right) x_{ij} \\ &= -\frac{1}{N} \sum_{i=1}^{N} \left(y_i^{(k)} - p_i^{(k)} \left(y_i^{(k)} + \sum_{\ell \neq k} y_i^{(\ell)}\right) \right) x_{ij} \\ & = \frac{1}{N} \sum_{i=1}^N (p_i^{(k)} - y_i^{(k)} ) x_{ij}. \end{align*} .

$p_i^{(k)}$ $\theta^{(k)}$ , $x_{ij}$ $y_i^{(k)}$ .

Linear Discriminant Analysis when $p = 1$

$Y$ $k$ , $X$ $f_k$ .

$$ f_k(x) = \frac{1}{\sqrt{2 \pi} \sigma_k} e^{ -\frac{1}{2} \left( \frac{x - \mu_k}{\sigma_k} \right)^2 } $$

$\mu_k$ , $\sigma_k^2$ .

$\sigma_k = \sigma$ .

Bayes $p_k(x) = \mathbb P (Y = k | X = x)$ .

$$ p_k (x) = \frac{\pi_k \frac{1}{\sqrt{2 \pi} \sigma} e^{-\frac{1}{2}\left( \frac{x - \mu_k}{\sigma} \right)^2}}{\sum_{l=1}^{K} \pi_l \frac{1}{\sqrt{2 \pi} \sigma} e^{-\frac{1}{2}\left( \frac{x - \mu_l}{\sigma} \right)^2}} $$

$X=x$ $p_k (x)$ .

, , discriminant score .

$$ \delta_k (x) = x \frac{\mu_k}{\sigma^2} - \frac{\mu_k^2}{2 \sigma^2} + \log (\pi_k) $$

$p_k$ $\delta_k$ .

$\delta_k$ $x$ .

$K=2$, $\pi_1 = \pi_2 = 0.5$ .

$$ x = \frac{\mu_1 + \mu_2}{2} $$

.

\begin{align*} \hat \pi_k &= \frac{n_k}{n} \\ \hat \mu_k &= \frac{1}{n_k} \sum_{i:y_i=k} x_i \\ \hat \sigma^2 &= \frac{1}{n-K} \sum_{k=1}^{K} \sum_{i:y_i=k}(x_i - \hat \mu_k)^2 \end{align*}

discriminant analysis

  • $f_k(x)$ Gaussian $\Sigma_{k}$ , quadratic discriminant analysis .

  • $f_k(x) = \prod_{j=1}^{p} f_{jk}(x_j)$, , $x$ , naive Bayes .

  • , $f_k$ discriminant analysis form .

Quadratic discriminant analysis

$$ \delta_k(x) = -\frac{1}{2} (x - \mu_k)^{\top} \Sigma_{k}^{-1} (x - \mu_k) - \frac{1}{2}\log |\Sigma_k| + \log \pi_k $$

$k$ $\Sigma_{k}$ , quadratic .

sklearn.discriminant_analysis.QuadraticDiscriminantAnalysis quadratic discriminant analysis .
